extends _templates/layout.pug
block preloader
	.preloader.color-2
block content
	.snj-container-fluid.project-page
		.row
			section.project-about
				//- .background-wrapper.p-about-bg
				.info-wrapper.snj-col-10.offset-1.snj-col-md-4.offset-md-4
					h2.subtitle-block Content Creation & Management
					h1.project-title Puma
					span 01
				aside.especifications.snj-col-10.offset-1.snj-col-md-6.offset-md-3
					.snj-row
						div.especific-item.snj-col-md-2
							h4 Cliente
							h5 Puma						
						div.especific-item.offset-md-2.snj-col-md-4
							h4 Project
							h5 Social brand building
						div.especific-item.snj-col-md-2.offset-md-2
							h4 Year
							h5 2017
			section.project-description
				.snj-col-10.offset-1.snj-col-md-6.offset-md-3
					h1.project-title Puma
					div.paragraph-left
						p We worked with PUMA Middle East to create the brand’s first non-global Instagram account: <a (href="")>@pumame</a>. 
						p It was an opportunity we had to pitch internally to PUMA global, and came with significant risks. Basically, if we messed up, we mess up the opportunity for every other country/region in the world that want their own IG account.
					div.paragraph-right
						p Thankfully, we did the opposite and he success of the account has led to several local accounts around the world, from India to South Africa. 
						p We manage the <a (href="")>@pumame </a> account completely: strategy, content production, community management and reporting. In just a few years, the account reach over 100k followers and continues to “put on” for the region’s own talent, from photographers to musicians. 


